  "title": "Essex EEG Movie Memory dataset",
  "description": "This dataset comprises raw electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from 27 participants acquired during a movie memory recognition task. Participants viewed 10-second film clips previously watched and provided recognition and memory judgments, with recognized clips shown a second time for temporal annotation of memory cues. The study investigates neural correlates of video memorability using high-density EEG recording.",
  "methods_description": "EEG data were acquired using a BioSemi ActiveTwo system with 64 electrodes positioned according to the international 10-20 system at a sampling rate of 2048 Hz.",
